  "text": "Inspecting of several bark and wood samples of dead or dying Pinus sp. in city of Tehran collected on late 2016-early 2017, yielded three ektaphelenchids, one of which was recently described as Cryptaphelenchus varicaudatus [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The two other species belonged to one new and a known species of the respective genera Ektaphelenchus and Devibursaphelenchus and are studied and illustrated in present paper.",
